WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.952 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.952 --> 00:00:08.946 align:middle line:90%
[HORN]

00:00:08.946 --> 00:00:13.916 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.916 --> 00:00:15.407 align:middle line:90%
[HORN]

00:00:15.407 --> 00:00:22.400 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:24.440 align:middle line:84%
>> There should be,
somewhere upon Earth,

00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:28.370 align:middle line:84%
a place that no nation could
claim as its sole property,

00:00:28.370 --> 00:00:31.280 align:middle line:84%
a place where all human
beings have goodwill,

00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:35.030 align:middle line:84%
sincere in their aspiration,
could live freely as citizens

00:00:35.030 --> 00:00:38.000 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.710 align:middle line:84%
That was mother's
dream as early as 1954.

00:00:40.710 --> 00:00:49.055 align:middle line:90%
[BIRDS SINGING]

00:00:49.055 --> 00:00:52.548 align:middle line:90%
[GONG]

00:00:52.548 --> 00:01:11.688 align:middle line:90%
>> [VOCALIZATION]

00:01:11.688 --> 00:01:20.634 align:middle line:90%


00:01:20.634 --> 00:01:24.630 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING BOWL RINGS]

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:26.850 align:middle line:84%
>> You have to leave
the outside world.

00:01:26.850 --> 00:01:29.410 align:middle line:84%
You have to enter
another spirit.

00:01:29.410 --> 00:01:33.180 align:middle line:84%
You have to go really
inside, internal.

00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:34.770 align:middle line:90%
You work internal.

00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:37.050 align:middle line:84%
For me, this place
is a laboratory.

00:01:37.050 --> 00:01:38.370 align:middle line:90%
You jump in.

00:01:38.370 --> 00:01:39.870 align:middle line:90%
You have a white skin.

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:44.270 align:middle line:84%
You jump in it, and you
might be orange and yellow.

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:47.460 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm trying to say?

00:01:47.460 --> 00:01:51.150 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what all
of it is, actually.

00:01:51.150 --> 00:01:53.970 align:middle line:84%
I try to understand
it from my heart.

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:58.353 align:middle line:84%
It's hard to explain to somebody
that comes new here and says,

00:01:58.353 --> 00:01:59.520 align:middle line:90%
what is this supposed to be?

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:00.320 align:middle line:90%
A city?

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:03.630 align:middle line:84%
You know, like, oh, you know,
where's the city, actually?

00:02:03.630 --> 00:02:07.550 align:middle line:84%
Where's the mall and
the shopping center?

00:02:07.550 --> 00:02:11.310 align:middle line:84%
And I say, hey, then you go to
Madras, you go to Bangalore,

00:02:11.310 --> 00:02:13.100 align:middle line:90%
or you go somewhere else.

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:15.060 align:middle line:90%
That's not the city for that.

00:02:15.060 --> 00:02:19.720 align:middle line:84%
The city is here for
a consciousness, for--

00:02:19.720 --> 00:02:24.950 align:middle line:84%
to aspire something that
maybe was in the very,

00:02:24.950 --> 00:02:27.020 align:middle line:90%
very back of your mind.

00:02:27.020 --> 00:02:32.240 align:middle line:84%
Another life, another
system, another society.

00:02:32.240 --> 00:02:33.680 align:middle line:90%
Try to see it that way.

00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:36.656 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:36.656 --> 00:03:01.970 align:middle line:90%


00:03:01.970 --> 00:03:03.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Western model [NON-ENGLISH].

00:03:03.570 --> 00:03:07.480 align:middle line:10%
>> Here is the model of the city
as it is conceived for 50,000

00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:08.670 align:middle line:10%
people.

00:03:08.670 --> 00:03:10.980 align:middle line:84%
In the center stands
the Matrimandir,

00:03:10.980 --> 00:03:14.980 align:middle line:84%
where one goes to concentrate
and become self aware.

00:03:14.980 --> 00:03:17.790 align:middle line:84%
But-- and this is
important to clarify--

00:03:17.790 --> 00:03:20.690 align:middle line:90%
it is not a temple.

00:03:20.690 --> 00:03:24.990 align:middle line:84%
The different zones of the city
converge towards its center,

00:03:24.990 --> 00:03:27.225 align:middle line:84%
and likewise, from
there, radiate outwards.

00:03:27.225 --> 00:03:29.850 align:middle line:90%


00:03:29.850 --> 00:03:32.130 align:middle line:84%
There will be 12
gardens surrounding

00:03:32.130 --> 00:03:35.760 align:middle line:84%
the Matrimandir, each with
its own specific psychological

00:03:35.760 --> 00:03:37.530 align:middle line:90%
symbolism.

00:03:37.530 --> 00:03:39.840 align:middle line:10%
And there we find
the amphitheater,

00:03:39.840 --> 00:03:43.350 align:middle line:10%
where on the 28th
of February, 1968,

00:03:43.350 --> 00:03:46.110 align:middle line:10%
a handful of soil from most
of the countries of the Earth

00:03:46.110 --> 00:03:48.540 align:middle line:10%
was placed in an
urn to symbolize

00:03:48.540 --> 00:03:50.550 align:middle line:10%
that the entire
city was dedicated

00:03:50.550 --> 00:03:53.600 align:middle line:10%
to international
understanding and human unity.

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:58.490 align:middle line:90%


00:03:58.490 --> 00:04:01.860 align:middle line:84%
>> The Matrimandir has now been
under construction for more

00:04:01.860 --> 00:04:03.660 align:middle line:90%
than 30 years.

00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:06.990 align:middle line:84%
Models that are still like
music from the future.

00:04:06.990 --> 00:04:09.540 align:middle line:84%
One expects to be
entering an ideal city,

00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:12.630 align:middle line:84%
with all its ideological
and geographical contours

00:04:12.630 --> 00:04:14.250 align:middle line:90%
neatly defined.

00:04:14.250 --> 00:04:16.029 align:middle line:90%
It is nothing like that.

00:04:16.029 --> 00:04:17.909 align:middle line:84%
The place is simply
a field of becoming.

00:04:17.909 --> 00:04:19.604 align:middle line:90%


00:04:19.604 --> 00:04:20.999 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:04:20.999 --> 00:04:24.254 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, wow!

00:04:24.254 --> 00:04:25.860 align:middle line:90%
Fantastic!

00:04:25.860 --> 00:04:29.430 align:middle line:84%
There was no water, and
then all night, it just

00:04:29.430 --> 00:04:31.097 align:middle line:90%
soaks in and makes--

00:04:31.097 --> 00:04:32.410 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:04:32.410 --> 00:04:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH], OK.

00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:36.010 align:middle line:84%
And you see how
different the soil is?

00:04:36.010 --> 00:04:36.810 align:middle line:90%
Do you see?

00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:38.996 align:middle line:84%
Here it's red, and then
it becomes clay-like.

00:04:38.996 --> 00:04:40.538 align:middle line:84%
Do you want me to
put you down there?

00:04:40.538 --> 00:04:41.526 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:04:41.526 --> 00:04:48.442 align:middle line:90%


00:04:48.442 --> 00:04:52.660 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH CHATTER]

00:04:52.660 --> 00:04:53.770 align:middle line:90%


00:04:53.770 --> 00:04:55.880 align:middle line:90%
>> When Auroville changed a lot.

00:04:55.880 --> 00:04:57.710 align:middle line:84%
Many things happened
for a long time,

00:04:57.710 --> 00:04:59.810 align:middle line:84%
there were about only
500 people in Auroville.

00:04:59.810 --> 00:05:02.510 align:middle line:84%
And then I think now
there's nearly 2,000,

00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:06.380 align:middle line:90%
so suddenly it has changed.

00:05:06.380 --> 00:05:09.080 align:middle line:10%
And then I went to America,
and I lived in America

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:10.470 align:middle line:10%
for 14 years.

00:05:10.470 --> 00:05:12.160 align:middle line:10%
>> When did you go to America?

00:05:12.160 --> 00:05:14.076 align:middle line:10%
>> I left in 1987.

00:05:14.076 --> 00:05:19.090 align:middle line:84%
And I lived in Oakland,
just near San Francisco.

00:05:19.090 --> 00:05:25.625 align:middle line:84%
And I met Paul, and we
have a wood workshop,

00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:28.460 align:middle line:84%
and we build
furniture with that.

00:05:28.460 --> 00:05:33.980 align:middle line:84%
So it was interesting
for me to leave Auroville

00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:38.150 align:middle line:90%
and to go and be in the world.

00:05:38.150 --> 00:05:40.130 align:middle line:90%
And it was a long process.

00:05:40.130 --> 00:05:42.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean learning,
also coming from here

00:05:42.220 --> 00:05:45.560 align:middle line:84%
and not having diplomas
and this and that

00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:47.690 align:middle line:90%
and just having life experience.

00:05:47.690 --> 00:05:50.340 align:middle line:84%
But I realized that I
had a lot of experience.

00:05:50.340 --> 00:05:53.620 align:middle line:84%
I worked as a banker,
I did planting trees,

00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:55.790 align:middle line:84%
I worked all around
Auroville all of the time,

00:05:55.790 --> 00:05:58.190 align:middle line:84%
doing many different
things, but I never

00:05:58.190 --> 00:06:01.400 align:middle line:84%
got a paper for any
of the things I did.

00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:04.850 align:middle line:84%
So when you're in the West,
where those things are

00:06:04.850 --> 00:06:10.250 align:middle line:84%
important, it was always
a little bit difficult.

00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:15.770 align:middle line:84%
It's only in the end for me
that I found that I really

00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:19.480 align:middle line:84%
could recognize and appreciate
what Auroville had given me.

00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:24.445 align:middle line:84%
Because I was more flexible,
and you know, so all of that

00:06:24.445 --> 00:06:25.245 align:middle line:90%
was a lot easier.

00:06:25.245 --> 00:06:26.045 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:26.045 --> 00:06:27.358 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:06:27.358 --> 00:06:29.302 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:06:29.302 --> 00:06:40.490 align:middle line:90%


00:06:40.490 --> 00:06:43.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Education will be based on
what we hope to receive from

00:06:43.370 --> 00:06:47.240 align:middle line:84%
the future, not what we
think we know of the past.

00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:49.040 align:middle line:84%
Mother, the founder
of Auroville,

00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:50.780 align:middle line:84%
set her goals high
for a modern form

00:06:50.780 --> 00:06:52.520 align:middle line:90%
of educational experimentalism.

00:06:52.520 --> 00:06:56.300 align:middle line:84%
Education touches all the
aspects and dimensions

00:06:56.300 --> 00:06:59.540 align:middle line:84%
of the human being, the
physical, vital, mental,

00:06:59.540 --> 00:07:01.700 align:middle line:90%
psychic, and spiritual.

00:07:01.700 --> 00:07:05.120 align:middle line:84%
There are, nonetheless, a
variety of schooling systems.

00:07:05.120 --> 00:07:07.460 align:middle line:84%
There's a number of schools
taking youth from the Tamil

00:07:07.460 --> 00:07:09.720 align:middle line:90%
villages surrounding Auroville.

00:07:09.720 --> 00:07:12.380 align:middle line:84%
A retired British
Navy man, for example,

00:07:12.380 --> 00:07:14.810 align:middle line:84%
decided to create an
educational environment

00:07:14.810 --> 00:07:17.840 align:middle line:84%
for some of the poorest children
from the villages, which

00:07:17.840 --> 00:07:21.110 align:middle line:84%
he has managed to do with the
financial support of Auroville,

00:07:21.110 --> 00:07:22.630 align:middle line:90%
while remaining independent.

00:07:22.630 --> 00:07:26.490 align:middle line:90%


00:07:26.490 --> 00:07:28.500 align:middle line:84%
>> It took me seven
years to find the money,

00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:30.360 align:middle line:90%
but we did it eventually.

00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:32.290 align:middle line:90%
We're very pleased with it.

00:07:32.290 --> 00:07:36.130 align:middle line:84%
And we try to introduce
into the classrooms

00:07:36.130 --> 00:07:40.605 align:middle line:84%
the Western concept of a
classroom, where it's alive.

00:07:40.605 --> 00:07:45.590 align:middle line:90%


00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:50.000 align:middle line:10%
It's not just a sterile
room, it's living.

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:55.050 align:middle line:10%
Not only with their work, but
with their decoration as well.

00:07:55.050 --> 00:07:57.230 align:middle line:84%
We're very careful
not to destroy, not

00:07:57.230 --> 00:08:01.010 align:middle line:84%
to even try to destroy
any of their culture.

00:08:01.010 --> 00:08:02.960 align:middle line:84%
We just want to
superimpose a little bit

00:08:02.960 --> 00:08:06.960 align:middle line:84%
of something else,
no more than that.

00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:10.250 align:middle line:84%
What we think are
the good parts of it.

00:08:10.250 --> 00:08:12.218 align:middle line:84%
Their own culture
is very important.

00:08:12.218 --> 00:08:14.510 align:middle line:84%
They're going to live here
for the rest of their lives.

00:08:14.510 --> 00:08:17.300 align:middle line:84%
Very few of them are
going to go anywhere else.

00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:20.220 align:middle line:90%


00:08:20.220 --> 00:08:22.088 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:08:22.088 --> 00:08:23.650 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:08:23.650 --> 00:08:26.400 align:middle line:90%


00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:27.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Here.

00:08:27.200 --> 00:08:31.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm not asking a point,
I'm asking to analyze.

00:08:31.080 --> 00:08:33.960 align:middle line:90%
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

00:08:33.960 --> 00:08:37.320 align:middle line:90%


00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:40.820 align:middle line:84%
>> The children from
the local villages.

00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:44.650 align:middle line:84%
They're very, very poor,
even by Indian standards.

00:08:44.650 --> 00:08:46.770 align:middle line:84%
Many of the parents
are illiterate,

00:08:46.770 --> 00:08:50.700 align:middle line:84%
and these children are the
first generation education.

00:08:50.700 --> 00:08:52.800 align:middle line:84%
They're lovely children,
beautiful children,

00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:54.300 align:middle line:90%
from the inside out.

00:08:54.300 --> 00:09:18.590 align:middle line:90%


00:09:18.590 --> 00:09:21.930 align:middle line:84%
I've become more attached
to Aurobindo and the Mother

00:09:21.930 --> 00:09:24.910 align:middle line:84%
since I've been here than
I was when I arrived.

00:09:24.910 --> 00:09:27.720 align:middle line:84%
I have learned their
value, their worth.

00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:29.970 align:middle line:84%
They're two very,
very wonderful people.

00:09:29.970 --> 00:09:33.170 align:middle line:84%
The Mother is a
stupendous person, really.

00:09:33.170 --> 00:09:36.050 align:middle line:90%
Her intellect amazes me.

00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:38.790 align:middle line:84%
I wish I could have met
her, but she was dead long,

00:09:38.790 --> 00:09:41.420 align:middle line:90%
long before I came here.

00:09:41.420 --> 00:09:46.160 align:middle line:84%
Yes, I can't pretend
that I was a devotee when

00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:47.710 align:middle line:90%
I came running out here.

00:09:47.710 --> 00:09:48.560 align:middle line:90%
That isn't so.

00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:55.670 align:middle line:90%


00:09:55.670 --> 00:09:59.200 align:middle line:84%
>> The structure that is closest
to Mother's dream is the Free

00:09:59.200 --> 00:10:00.730 align:middle line:90%
Progress School.

00:10:00.730 --> 00:10:03.010 align:middle line:84%
A school that does
not issue degrees,

00:10:03.010 --> 00:10:05.230 align:middle line:90%
give exams, or certificates.

00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:09.190 align:middle line:10%
>> The value of certification
is only to bring you success,

00:10:09.190 --> 00:10:13.240 align:middle line:10%
to bring you a good career, to
help you to earn more money.

00:10:13.240 --> 00:10:18.010 align:middle line:84%
Now, these aims tend to
be utilitarian and empty.

00:10:18.010 --> 00:10:22.360 align:middle line:10%
Real self-development, the
idea behind Auroville education

00:10:22.360 --> 00:10:25.435 align:middle line:10%
that Mother proposed,
she called Free Progress.

00:10:25.435 --> 00:10:27.970 align:middle line:10%


00:10:27.970 --> 00:10:31.810 align:middle line:10%
And Free Progress is
an education that is--

00:10:31.810 --> 00:10:34.480 align:middle line:10%
that wants to be guided
by the soul, that

00:10:34.480 --> 00:10:39.490 align:middle line:10%
is beyond above
habits, preconceptions,

00:10:39.490 --> 00:10:41.270 align:middle line:10%
and fixed ideas.

00:10:41.270 --> 00:10:44.860 align:middle line:84%
So in that sense, it's
not necessarily free.

00:10:44.860 --> 00:10:47.290 align:middle line:90%
The main word is progress.

00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:51.310 align:middle line:84%
But the manner in which
you progress is free.

00:10:51.310 --> 00:10:53.830 align:middle line:84%
The idea is that as
soon as possible,

00:10:53.830 --> 00:10:59.350 align:middle line:84%
a young person, recognizing that
a young person, even a child,

00:10:59.350 --> 00:11:02.800 align:middle line:84%
is complete, has the capacity
for self-discipline, which

00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:05.170 align:middle line:90%
is innate in every human being.

00:11:05.170 --> 00:11:08.440 align:middle line:84%
The sooner you can
empower the child

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:14.710 align:middle line:84%
to find this innate capacity,
the sooner you allow him to--

00:11:14.710 --> 00:11:19.030 align:middle line:84%
or her-- to make his best
contribution in the world.

00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:29.760 align:middle line:90%


00:11:29.760 --> 00:11:31.590 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:11:31.590 --> 00:11:34.320 align:middle line:84%
>> It is an open,
free education.

00:11:34.320 --> 00:11:36.950 align:middle line:10%
Now I'm going to a math
class, but if I do not

00:11:36.950 --> 00:11:39.620 align:middle line:10%
feel like doing what
the others are studying,

00:11:39.620 --> 00:11:43.490 align:middle line:10%
I can go to physics or go and
observe flowers and nature,

00:11:43.490 --> 00:11:44.690 align:middle line:10%
whatever.

00:11:44.690 --> 00:11:46.419 align:middle line:90%
We are free in everything.

00:11:46.419 --> 00:11:59.410 align:middle line:90%


00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:00.966 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:12:00.966 --> 00:12:03.530 align:middle line:90%


00:12:03.530 --> 00:12:06.560 align:middle line:84%
>> We are all the
divine in evolution.

00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:10.170 align:middle line:10%
We are here for a progressive
transformation of our being.

00:12:10.170 --> 00:12:13.970 align:middle line:10%
And such a transformation is
so enormous that it cannot be

00:12:13.970 --> 00:12:17.040 align:middle line:10%
accomplished by an
individual alone,

00:12:17.040 --> 00:12:20.960 align:middle line:10%
no matter how spiritually
evolved he might be.

00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:23.630 align:middle line:84%
Luckily, there is a
new evolutionary force

00:12:23.630 --> 00:12:27.190 align:middle line:84%
at work on Earth, that Sri
Aurobindo and Mother called,

00:12:27.190 --> 00:12:28.940 align:middle line:84%
because one has to,
after all, give things

00:12:28.940 --> 00:12:31.680 align:middle line:90%
a name, the supermental.

00:12:31.680 --> 00:12:35.820 align:middle line:84%
The evolutionary force that
comes after that of the mind.

00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:37.190 align:middle line:90%
We have lived humanity.

00:12:37.190 --> 00:12:41.070 align:middle line:84%
We have incarnated and lived
the reign of mind's powers.

00:12:41.070 --> 00:12:44.660 align:middle line:84%
We have explored its farthest
reaches and possibilities,

00:12:44.660 --> 00:12:47.420 align:middle line:84%
and now the reign of the
mind is drawing to a close,

00:12:47.420 --> 00:12:52.100 align:middle line:84%
because a new evolutionary force
is activating itself on Earth

00:12:52.100 --> 00:12:53.750 align:middle line:90%
in a more and more visible way.

00:12:53.750 --> 00:13:03.830 align:middle line:90%


00:13:03.830 --> 00:13:06.110 align:middle line:84%
>> According to the
charter of Auroville,

00:13:06.110 --> 00:13:08.630 align:middle line:84%
the whole city is a site
of unending progress

00:13:08.630 --> 00:13:10.340 align:middle line:90%
and education.

00:13:10.340 --> 00:13:13.430 align:middle line:84%
Along with her colleagues at
the Laboratory of Evolution,

00:13:13.430 --> 00:13:16.130 align:middle line:84%
Barker represents, in
some way, the memory

00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:19.820 align:middle line:84%
of the texts of Sri
Aurobindo and Mother.

00:13:19.820 --> 00:13:22.430 align:middle line:84%
In the center of
research, one can also

00:13:22.430 --> 00:13:27.200 align:middle line:84%
find works on psychology,
philosophy, esotericism,

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:29.490 align:middle line:90%
and even medicine.

00:13:29.490 --> 00:13:33.140 align:middle line:84%
However, there are times when
these aspirations that seek

00:13:33.140 --> 00:13:37.400 align:middle line:84%
for the realization of a better
world cannot impede reality

00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:39.010 align:middle line:90%
from intruding on these ideals.

00:13:39.010 --> 00:13:55.388 align:middle line:90%


00:13:55.388 --> 00:13:56.885 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi.

00:13:56.885 --> 00:14:00.877 align:middle line:84%
Did you guys see a bunch
of people over there?

00:14:00.877 --> 00:14:02.873 align:middle line:90%
Just around the corner, here.

00:14:02.873 --> 00:14:05.162 align:middle line:90%
Have you seen them pass by?

00:14:05.162 --> 00:14:07.620 align:middle line:84%
There was a whole group, and
I think they were a bit drunk,

00:14:07.620 --> 00:14:07.910 align:middle line:90%
maybe.

00:14:07.910 --> 00:14:09.450 align:middle line:84%
>> They didn't come
this way, you know?

00:14:09.450 --> 00:14:10.250 align:middle line:90%
I don't think so.

00:14:10.250 --> 00:14:11.917 align:middle line:84%
>> I think you should
go behind me then.

00:14:11.917 --> 00:14:12.717 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:14:12.717 --> 00:14:13.850 align:middle line:90%
Then we go in five minutes?

00:14:13.850 --> 00:14:14.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:14:14.650 --> 00:14:15.450 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:14:15.450 --> 00:14:17.375 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:14:17.375 --> 00:14:19.920 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:22.710 align:middle line:10%
>> There was a time, about
five to six years ago,

00:14:22.710 --> 00:14:25.560 align:middle line:10%
when people would come from
Pondicherry to drink alcohol

00:14:25.560 --> 00:14:28.890 align:middle line:10%
in Auroville in the
neighboring cashew fields.

00:14:28.890 --> 00:14:31.590 align:middle line:84%
This created disturbances,
as obviously alcohol

00:14:31.590 --> 00:14:33.570 align:middle line:84%
creates violence,
and some people

00:14:33.570 --> 00:14:35.790 align:middle line:90%
were aggressed on the roads.

00:14:35.790 --> 00:14:38.250 align:middle line:84%
As a result, a service
was spontaneously

00:14:38.250 --> 00:14:41.570 align:middle line:90%
started composed of volunteers.

00:14:41.570 --> 00:14:45.060 align:middle line:84%
We all trained in martial
arts, and our physical presence

00:14:45.060 --> 00:14:49.330 align:middle line:84%
on the roads is such that it
has become a dissuasive factor.

00:14:49.330 --> 00:14:50.850 align:middle line:84%
And those type of
people no longer

00:14:50.850 --> 00:14:54.630 align:middle line:84%
come to perturb the
atmosphere of Auroville.

00:14:54.630 --> 00:14:56.910 align:middle line:84%
One must clearly bear
in mind that Auroville

00:14:56.910 --> 00:15:01.380 align:middle line:84%
is based on human relations, on
understanding and unity, which

00:15:01.380 --> 00:15:03.390 align:middle line:90%
is why it is understood.

00:15:03.390 --> 00:15:06.670 align:middle line:84%
We do not have a police
force in Auroville as such.

00:15:06.670 --> 00:15:09.180 align:middle line:84%
We are supposed to do
everything ourselves.

00:15:09.180 --> 00:15:11.850 align:middle line:90%
So as you see, we are not armed.

00:15:11.850 --> 00:15:13.770 align:middle line:84%
We only carry
torches to illuminate

00:15:13.770 --> 00:15:14.910 align:middle line:90%
the road, that's all.

00:15:14.910 --> 00:15:21.600 align:middle line:90%


00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:24.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Utopias, ideals,
alternatives.

00:15:24.850 --> 00:15:27.690 align:middle line:84%
These are all words
that inspire reflection.

00:15:27.690 --> 00:15:31.350 align:middle line:90%
And not only in Aurovillians.

00:15:31.350 --> 00:15:34.700 align:middle line:84%
>> I think we need more such
interaction in the world,

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:36.120 align:middle line:90%
so people can understand.

00:15:36.120 --> 00:15:38.920 align:middle line:10%
A lot of misunderstanding
prevails.

00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:42.300 align:middle line:10%
I think the whole question of
intolerance, which is growing,

00:15:42.300 --> 00:15:46.110 align:middle line:10%
the violence in the human heart
is growing today in the world.

00:15:46.110 --> 00:15:48.710 align:middle line:84%
If you want to stop that
violence growing further

00:15:48.710 --> 00:15:51.750 align:middle line:84%
in the human heart,
we need to replace it

00:15:51.750 --> 00:15:55.860 align:middle line:84%
with harmony, understanding,
understanding of diversity

00:15:55.860 --> 00:15:59.190 align:middle line:84%
and pluralism in
human societies.

00:15:59.190 --> 00:16:00.840 align:middle line:10%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:02.910 align:middle line:10%
>> From the moment one
is capable of thinking

00:16:02.910 --> 00:16:06.060 align:middle line:10%
of tomorrow, it follows
naturally one has a dream

00:16:06.060 --> 00:16:07.530 align:middle line:10%
for tomorrow.

00:16:07.530 --> 00:16:09.480 align:middle line:90%
I know that tomorrow will be.

00:16:09.480 --> 00:16:12.030 align:middle line:90%
But only man is capable of this.

00:16:12.030 --> 00:16:15.255 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, one has a
duty to act in a way

00:16:15.255 --> 00:16:18.240 align:middle line:84%
that tomorrow will be
more pleasant than today.

00:16:18.240 --> 00:16:20.700 align:middle line:84%
Consequently, to
be Utopian is to be

00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:23.880 align:middle line:84%
faithful to one's duty as
a man and attuned to man's

00:16:23.880 --> 00:16:25.960 align:middle line:90%
extraordinary nature.

00:16:25.960 --> 00:16:28.095 align:middle line:84%
Thus, we all need
to create utopias.

00:16:28.095 --> 00:16:31.266 align:middle line:90%


00:16:31.266 --> 00:16:46.132 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:16:46.132 --> 00:16:48.960 align:middle line:90%


00:16:48.960 --> 00:16:49.920 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH].

00:16:49.920 --> 00:16:58.950 align:middle line:90%


00:16:58.950 --> 00:17:03.000 align:middle line:10%
>> The legend of Irumbai Temple
recounts how a yogi prayed

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:06.869 align:middle line:10%
for so long without stop in this
place that his body gave off

00:17:06.869 --> 00:17:09.750 align:middle line:10%
so much heat, that the
rains no longer fell.

00:17:09.750 --> 00:17:38.400 align:middle line:90%


00:17:38.400 --> 00:17:42.750 align:middle line:84%
The king was worried and sent
a dancing girl to distract him.

00:17:42.750 --> 00:17:45.630 align:middle line:84%
The yogi finally came
out of his meditation,

00:17:45.630 --> 00:17:47.910 align:middle line:90%
and the rains again fell.

00:17:47.910 --> 00:17:50.070 align:middle line:84%
The King then organized
a great celebration

00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:52.500 align:middle line:84%
at the Irumbai
Temple to celebrate

00:17:52.500 --> 00:17:54.210 align:middle line:90%
the end of the drought.

00:17:54.210 --> 00:17:55.180 align:middle line:90%
The dancer was present.

00:17:55.180 --> 00:18:15.770 align:middle line:90%


00:18:15.770 --> 00:18:20.220 align:middle line:84%
The yogi noticed that an anklet
was slipping off as she danced,

00:18:20.220 --> 00:18:23.110 align:middle line:84%
and he reached out
and reattached it.

00:18:23.110 --> 00:18:26.110 align:middle line:84%
All present then mocked him
for having debased himself

00:18:26.110 --> 00:18:28.750 align:middle line:84%
by touching the foot
of a dancing girl.

00:18:28.750 --> 00:18:33.130 align:middle line:84%
Furious, he declared that
the land would become barren.

00:18:33.130 --> 00:18:36.310 align:middle line:84%
The King implored him
to retract his curse,

00:18:36.310 --> 00:18:39.500 align:middle line:84%
but he replied, what
is done is done.

00:18:39.500 --> 00:18:42.940 align:middle line:84%
But one day, when people will
come from the eight directions

00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:47.000 align:middle line:84%
of the Earth, then the land will
become covered in forest again.

00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:53.500 align:middle line:90%


00:18:53.500 --> 00:18:54.450 align:middle line:90%
And so it was.

00:18:54.450 --> 00:19:00.360 align:middle line:90%


00:19:00.360 --> 00:19:03.030 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:19:03.030 --> 00:19:08.400 align:middle line:84%
>> This is a forest that we have
created over the last 30 years.

00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:10.960 align:middle line:90%
The land was arid and dry.

00:19:10.960 --> 00:19:15.180 align:middle line:84%
Over time, green
cover has returned.

00:19:15.180 --> 00:19:18.920 align:middle line:84%
One seems to be in the
midst of an ancient forest,

00:19:18.920 --> 00:19:22.320 align:middle line:90%
but in fact, it is a young one.

00:19:22.320 --> 00:19:25.705 align:middle line:10%
One could define it as a young,
tropical, evergreen forest.

00:19:25.705 --> 00:19:31.170 align:middle line:90%


00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.010 align:middle line:84%
The birds have extended
their territory,

00:19:33.010 --> 00:19:36.700 align:middle line:84%
and other animals
have returned as well.

00:19:36.700 --> 00:19:40.540 align:middle line:84%
Large animals, like tigers
or elephants, are missing,

00:19:40.540 --> 00:19:42.430 align:middle line:84%
but Auroville is still
too small for them.

00:19:42.430 --> 00:20:01.125 align:middle line:90%


00:20:01.125 --> 00:20:03.750 align:middle line:10%
>> To be out here in the middle
of this sort of empty landscape

00:20:03.750 --> 00:20:06.840 align:middle line:10%
and watch the sun come up
and down a few hundred times,

00:20:06.840 --> 00:20:11.100 align:middle line:10%
and feel the rain, and
understand the seasons,

00:20:11.100 --> 00:20:14.732 align:middle line:10%
to understand the rhythms,
that was what the teacher was.

00:20:14.732 --> 00:20:15.690 align:middle line:90%
They were the teachers.

00:20:15.690 --> 00:20:16.990 align:middle line:90%
The elements were the teachers.

00:20:16.990 --> 00:20:18.240 align:middle line:90%
The seasons were the teachers.

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:20.460 align:middle line:90%
And the people also.

00:20:20.460 --> 00:20:22.410 align:middle line:10%
And of course, the people that--

00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:25.530 align:middle line:10%
the friends in the village,
they taught us how to plow

00:20:25.530 --> 00:20:29.070 align:middle line:10%
and what was good compost,
and what was good seed.

00:20:29.070 --> 00:20:33.120 align:middle line:84%
And they were our
first teachers.

00:20:33.120 --> 00:20:38.310 align:middle line:84%
This next step is taking
the experience out there

00:20:38.310 --> 00:20:41.760 align:middle line:84%
into Tamil Nadu and
working with the people who

00:20:41.760 --> 00:20:47.860 align:middle line:84%
have the power to make big
changes, the Forest Department.

00:20:47.860 --> 00:20:51.240 align:middle line:84%
And so it's to
develop a strategy.

00:20:51.240 --> 00:20:53.690 align:middle line:84%
If it's good enough, and if
the patterns are good enough,

00:20:53.690 --> 00:20:55.260 align:middle line:84%
if the techniques
are good enough,

00:20:55.260 --> 00:20:57.525 align:middle line:84%
then hopefully the
Forest Department,

00:20:57.525 --> 00:21:02.340 align:middle line:84%
that means the government,
will adopt it and on a big way

00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:04.890 align:middle line:84%
and start to bring back
maybe thousands, thousands,

00:21:04.890 --> 00:21:06.720 align:middle line:90%
millions of acres.

00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:08.342 align:middle line:90%
That's the dream.

00:21:08.342 --> 00:21:09.830 align:middle line:90%
[CAR HORN]

00:21:09.830 --> 00:21:15.300 align:middle line:90%


00:21:15.300 --> 00:21:18.840 align:middle line:84%
>> All over this place, you
see the residual waste from

00:21:18.840 --> 00:21:22.890 align:middle line:84%
the so-called compost, which
the farmers of our neighboring

00:21:22.890 --> 00:21:25.440 align:middle line:90%
village bring to this land.

00:21:25.440 --> 00:21:27.840 align:middle line:90%
Actually, it is town waste.

00:21:27.840 --> 00:21:29.550 align:middle line:90%
It is municipal waste.

00:21:29.550 --> 00:21:33.270 align:middle line:84%
Mixed waste without any
treatment, without any sorting.

00:21:33.270 --> 00:21:36.910 align:middle line:84%
And for them, it is the
cheapest source of compost,

00:21:36.910 --> 00:21:38.860 align:middle line:90%
so they bring it here.

00:21:38.860 --> 00:21:40.860 align:middle line:84%
And it was in '92,
when I was still

00:21:40.860 --> 00:21:43.740 align:middle line:84%
working as a medical doctor,
as a physician in the Auroville

00:21:43.740 --> 00:21:47.190 align:middle line:84%
Health Center, when we
observed an enormous fly

00:21:47.190 --> 00:21:49.050 align:middle line:90%
nuisance in one summer.

00:21:49.050 --> 00:21:51.510 align:middle line:10%
And later in the
same year, I had

00:21:51.510 --> 00:21:55.770 align:middle line:10%
to diagnose a much higher
number of typhoid cases

00:21:55.770 --> 00:21:57.550 align:middle line:10%
than ever before.

00:21:57.550 --> 00:22:02.490 align:middle line:84%
So we had to assume that
these typhoid cases were

00:22:02.490 --> 00:22:07.140 align:middle line:84%
linked to the flies
and to this garbage.

00:22:07.140 --> 00:22:10.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Like many Aurovillians, Lucas
does not pursue the profession

00:22:10.620 --> 00:22:14.550 align:middle line:84%
for which he studied and
obtained university degrees.

00:22:14.550 --> 00:22:17.310 align:middle line:84%
His path has led him to
change his focus from treating

00:22:17.310 --> 00:22:20.010 align:middle line:90%
symptoms to preventive action.

00:22:20.010 --> 00:22:23.310 align:middle line:84%
On his experimental farm,
he is testing and refining

00:22:23.310 --> 00:22:26.620 align:middle line:84%
the use of natural
pesticides for cashew trees,

00:22:26.620 --> 00:22:30.630 align:middle line:84%
an important cash crop for local
farmers, who do not take easily

00:22:30.630 --> 00:22:32.460 align:middle line:90%
to his methods.

00:22:32.460 --> 00:22:34.170 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:22:34.170 --> 00:22:35.850 align:middle line:90%
>> What are you doing?

00:22:35.850 --> 00:22:38.250 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm spraying pesticides.

00:22:38.250 --> 00:22:39.640 align:middle line:90%
>> What type?

00:22:39.640 --> 00:22:42.070 align:middle line:90%
>> We use DDT.

00:22:42.070 --> 00:22:44.280 align:middle line:90%
>> On what type of trees?

00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:45.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Cashew trees.

00:22:45.950 --> 00:22:49.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you know that is
dangerous for the environment?

00:22:49.500 --> 00:22:52.710 align:middle line:90%
>> I know, but everyone uses it.

00:22:52.710 --> 00:22:54.480 align:middle line:90%
So what to do?

00:22:54.480 --> 00:22:58.140 align:middle line:84%
I use it so the pests go
elsewhere to other fields.

00:22:58.140 --> 00:23:01.160 align:middle line:84%
If I am the only one
to stop using DDT,

00:23:01.160 --> 00:23:05.010 align:middle line:84%
then the insects will all
come and attack my trees.

00:23:05.010 --> 00:23:08.250 align:middle line:84%
If we all use DDT, the
pests will go elsewhere.

00:23:08.250 --> 00:23:21.462 align:middle line:90%


00:23:21.462 --> 00:23:52.092 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:23:52.092 --> 00:23:56.044 align:middle line:90%
[BELL]

00:23:56.044 --> 00:24:00.020 align:middle line:90%


00:24:00.020 --> 00:24:04.120 align:middle line:84%
>> The ecological point of
view is still an elite one,

00:24:04.120 --> 00:24:06.670 align:middle line:84%
even if in Auroville, as
elsewhere in the world,

00:24:06.670 --> 00:24:09.210 align:middle line:84%
one is trying to make
it more widespread.

00:24:09.210 --> 00:24:12.580 align:middle line:84%
The use of renewable
energies is an essential area

00:24:12.580 --> 00:24:15.670 align:middle line:84%
of research in Auroville,
whether on an individual

00:24:15.670 --> 00:24:17.500 align:middle line:90%
or a collective level.

00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:20.000 align:middle line:90%
One example is a solar kitchen.

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:22.750 align:middle line:84%
This is a community
kitchen that prepares up

00:24:22.750 --> 00:24:25.030 align:middle line:90%
to 1,000 meals a day.

00:24:25.030 --> 00:24:27.130 align:middle line:84%
The emphasis is
on steam cooking,

00:24:27.130 --> 00:24:29.810 align:middle line:84%
with the steam produced
from solar energy.

00:24:29.810 --> 00:24:34.870 align:middle line:84%
>> At noon, this reflector here
receives 175 kilowatts of free

00:24:34.870 --> 00:24:37.070 align:middle line:90%
energy from the sun.

00:24:37.070 --> 00:24:39.730 align:middle line:84%
Now we can harvest
about 40% of it.

00:24:39.730 --> 00:24:42.580 align:middle line:90%


00:24:42.580 --> 00:24:47.020 align:middle line:84%
What we have here is a
spherical concentrator.

00:24:47.020 --> 00:24:49.710 align:middle line:84%
The center of the
sphere is here,

00:24:49.710 --> 00:24:53.770 align:middle line:90%
and the radius is 8 meters, 60.

00:24:53.770 --> 00:24:58.110 align:middle line:10%
The sun will reflect in every
one of the 11,000 mirrors.

00:24:58.110 --> 00:25:01.810 align:middle line:10%
And each one of these
11,000 reflected sun rays

00:25:01.810 --> 00:25:05.440 align:middle line:10%
is intercepted by the receiver.

00:25:05.440 --> 00:25:07.930 align:middle line:84%
Computer makes a
difference between where

00:25:07.930 --> 00:25:11.680 align:middle line:84%
the sun and where is
the arm and then decides

00:25:11.680 --> 00:25:16.030 align:middle line:84%
to make-- to produce impulses
for the stepper motors

00:25:16.030 --> 00:25:20.020 align:middle line:84%
to bring the arm in
line with the sun.

00:25:20.020 --> 00:25:22.600 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:26.620 align:middle line:84%
>> We strive our utmost to use
mainly alternative technologies

00:25:26.620 --> 00:25:29.650 align:middle line:84%
in order to safeguard
the environment.

00:25:29.650 --> 00:25:32.260 align:middle line:10%
The windmill powers
the water pump.

00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:35.540 align:middle line:10%
We mix cow dung with
water to produce methane,

00:25:35.540 --> 00:25:37.030 align:middle line:10%
which we use for cooking gas.

00:25:37.030 --> 00:25:39.880 align:middle line:90%


00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:43.720 align:middle line:84%
Our electricity is produced
by photovoltaic panels

00:25:43.720 --> 00:25:46.160 align:middle line:84%
which provide us with
approximately 900 watts

00:25:46.160 --> 00:25:46.960 align:middle line:90%
per day.

00:25:46.960 --> 00:25:55.100 align:middle line:90%


00:25:55.100 --> 00:25:55.900 align:middle line:90%
>> There we are.

00:25:55.900 --> 00:26:00.640 align:middle line:90%


00:26:00.640 --> 00:26:02.110 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:26:02.110 --> 00:26:05.360 align:middle line:84%
>> 20 years ago, the
soil was very different.

00:26:05.360 --> 00:26:08.140 align:middle line:84%
It was eroded, and
the trees were scarce.

00:26:08.140 --> 00:26:09.320 align:middle line:90%
It was almost a desert.

00:26:09.320 --> 00:26:12.080 align:middle line:90%


00:26:12.080 --> 00:26:14.530 align:middle line:84%
We didn't have much
money back then.

00:26:14.530 --> 00:26:18.370 align:middle line:84%
We built slowly, bit by
bit, contenting ourselves

00:26:18.370 --> 00:26:21.580 align:middle line:90%
with what was possible.

00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:24.820 align:middle line:84%
Auroville did not
grow because of money.

00:26:24.820 --> 00:26:27.150 align:middle line:84%
Everything was built
in an ecological way.

00:26:27.150 --> 00:26:40.180 align:middle line:90%


00:26:40.180 --> 00:26:43.060 align:middle line:84%
Along with the farm, we
have a carpentry workshop

00:26:43.060 --> 00:26:45.505 align:middle line:84%
that employs 10 to
12 regular workers.

00:26:45.505 --> 00:26:53.590 align:middle line:90%


00:26:53.590 --> 00:26:56.410 align:middle line:84%
Most people here
are self-taught.

00:26:56.410 --> 00:26:57.890 align:middle line:90%
Well, at least I am.

00:26:57.890 --> 00:27:00.220 align:middle line:84%
I am a self-taught
country person.

00:27:00.220 --> 00:27:04.060 align:middle line:84%
This is also true as regards
to the construction business.

00:27:04.060 --> 00:27:08.220 align:middle line:84%
I am a builder, but I am
not a trained architect.

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:11.140 align:middle line:10%
A long time back, I
apprentice to be a mason,

00:27:11.140 --> 00:27:14.320 align:middle line:10%
but then here, everything
happens in its own way.

00:27:14.320 --> 00:27:17.170 align:middle line:10%
If you want to work,
certificates mean nothing.

00:27:17.170 --> 00:27:19.600 align:middle line:10%
What is important is know how.

00:27:19.600 --> 00:27:22.580 align:middle line:84%
You start off small,
and after 20 years,

00:27:22.580 --> 00:27:24.220 align:middle line:84%
you know how to build
yourself a house.

00:27:24.220 --> 00:27:41.410 align:middle line:90%


00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:44.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Auroville is trying to
bring back the ancient rural

00:27:44.320 --> 00:27:47.070 align:middle line:90%
knowledge of medicinal plants.

00:27:47.070 --> 00:27:49.750 align:middle line:84%
The Temple Groves are
invaluable resources

00:27:49.750 --> 00:27:54.010 align:middle line:84%
for the rediscovery of the
original herbs and plants.

00:27:54.010 --> 00:27:57.400 align:middle line:84%
They have survived the effects
of colonial deforestation.

00:27:57.400 --> 00:28:04.780 align:middle line:90%


00:28:04.780 --> 00:28:05.764 align:middle line:90%
>> What's this?

00:28:05.764 --> 00:28:11.023 align:middle line:90%


00:28:11.023 --> 00:28:12.356 align:middle line:90%
>> We've got a number of plants.

00:28:12.356 --> 00:28:14.202 align:middle line:90%
We've got leaves.

00:28:14.202 --> 00:28:15.660 align:middle line:84%
We've got some
medicine right here.

00:28:15.660 --> 00:28:16.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah?

00:28:16.480 --> 00:28:20.612 align:middle line:84%
>> People use this
for hunting termites.

00:28:20.612 --> 00:28:21.445 align:middle line:90%
>> Hunting termites?

00:28:21.445 --> 00:28:22.245 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:28:22.245 --> 00:28:23.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:28:23.140 --> 00:28:27.070 align:middle line:10%
>> And it's mixed with
other, that and chilies,

00:28:27.070 --> 00:28:30.370 align:middle line:10%
and dry them and burn them.

00:28:30.370 --> 00:28:32.770 align:middle line:10%
Put on top of the termite
nest, and the termite

00:28:32.770 --> 00:28:36.000 align:middle line:10%
comes for the smell, and
they will hunt for this.

00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:36.800 align:middle line:90%
>> And then what?

00:28:36.800 --> 00:28:37.880 align:middle line:90%
Did you eat the termites?

00:28:37.880 --> 00:28:38.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, people eat it.

00:28:38.950 --> 00:28:39.530 align:middle line:90%
>> They eat it?

00:28:39.530 --> 00:28:39.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:28:39.840 --> 00:28:40.700 align:middle line:90%
Flying termites.

00:28:40.700 --> 00:28:42.060 align:middle line:90%
>> This is the flying termites?

00:28:42.060 --> 00:28:42.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Flying termites.

00:28:42.770 --> 00:28:43.180 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:28:43.180 --> 00:28:43.980 align:middle line:90%
They are there.

00:28:43.980 --> 00:28:44.780 align:middle line:90%
I know those, yeah.

00:28:44.780 --> 00:28:45.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, those.

00:28:45.580 --> 00:28:47.050 align:middle line:84%
>> They have a
rich protein value.

00:28:47.050 --> 00:28:47.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:28:47.170 --> 00:28:48.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, yeah.

00:28:48.160 --> 00:28:55.585 align:middle line:90%


00:28:55.585 --> 00:29:05.010 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:29:05.010 --> 00:29:08.050 align:middle line:84%
>> The alternative model
also touches health through

00:29:08.050 --> 00:29:12.340 align:middle line:84%
the practices of homeopathy,
Ayurveda, and bioresonance,

00:29:12.340 --> 00:29:15.640 align:middle line:84%
in particular, as well as a
monthly visit of a Tibetan

00:29:15.640 --> 00:29:17.380 align:middle line:90%
doctor.

00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:21.670 align:middle line:84%
This multiple research makes the
Auroville reality seem at times

00:29:21.670 --> 00:29:23.410 align:middle line:90%
rather complex to the visitor.

00:29:23.410 --> 00:29:34.715 align:middle line:90%


00:29:34.715 --> 00:29:36.840 align:middle line:84%
>> I see a lot of journalists
that come and go from

00:29:36.840 --> 00:29:37.220 align:middle line:90%
Auroville.

00:29:37.220 --> 00:29:39.710 align:middle line:84%
I read a lot or what people read
about-- write about Auroville,

00:29:39.710 --> 00:29:41.418 align:middle line:84%
and I've seen a lot
of things that people

00:29:41.418 --> 00:29:42.350 align:middle line:90%
make about Auroville.

00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:44.433 align:middle line:10%
And it always strikes me
that the people who come,

00:29:44.433 --> 00:29:47.920 align:middle line:10%
they don't ever get inside and
see it from the inside out.

00:29:47.920 --> 00:29:49.670 align:middle line:84%
They always see it
objectively looking in.

00:29:49.670 --> 00:29:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And often, consequently,
the image that they project

00:29:53.360 --> 00:29:59.443 align:middle line:84%
isn't, to my mind,
too representative.

00:29:59.443 --> 00:30:03.230 align:middle line:90%


00:30:03.230 --> 00:30:04.220 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:30:04.220 --> 00:30:06.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Planet Earth is very small.

00:30:06.770 --> 00:30:08.780 align:middle line:10%
Now there are 6 billion of us.

00:30:08.780 --> 00:30:11.240 align:middle line:10%
Soon we will be 8 or 9 billion.

00:30:11.240 --> 00:30:14.150 align:middle line:10%
If it stops there, it
will remain livable,

00:30:14.150 --> 00:30:16.550 align:middle line:10%
but not under any conditions.

00:30:16.550 --> 00:30:19.910 align:middle line:84%
Earth can provide food for the
9 to 10 billion people who'll

00:30:19.910 --> 00:30:21.860 align:middle line:90%
be there at century's end.

00:30:21.860 --> 00:30:23.870 align:middle line:90%
There is no problem for food.

00:30:23.870 --> 00:30:26.540 align:middle line:84%
But there are problems in
relation to the price the Earth

00:30:26.540 --> 00:30:30.460 align:middle line:84%
has to pay, a price that she
cannot keep paying forever.

00:30:30.460 --> 00:30:34.400 align:middle line:10%
>> You can't do planning sitting
in a capital city for the whole

00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:38.810 align:middle line:10%
of the country, particularly in
India, with so much diversity.

00:30:38.810 --> 00:30:40.610 align:middle line:90%
So it has to be done.

00:30:40.610 --> 00:30:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Local level planning with
people's involvement,

00:30:43.680 --> 00:30:47.210 align:middle line:84%
and also you have to
give them training.

00:30:47.210 --> 00:30:51.080 align:middle line:84%
There are four important
things, training, technology,

00:30:51.080 --> 00:30:53.090 align:middle line:84%
appropriate technology,
environmentally,

00:30:53.090 --> 00:30:54.830 align:middle line:90%
that's why eco-technology.

00:30:54.830 --> 00:30:58.770 align:middle line:84%
The chair I hold for UNESCO,
it's called eco-technology.

00:30:58.770 --> 00:31:01.790 align:middle line:84%
Then it must also be
environmentally friendly,

00:31:01.790 --> 00:31:02.990 align:middle line:90%
economically viable.

00:31:02.990 --> 00:31:05.060 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, it won't
be applicable.

00:31:05.060 --> 00:31:08.820 align:middle line:84%
And so it is important
and socially equitable.

00:31:08.820 --> 00:31:09.830 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:12.950 align:middle line:84%
>> The price the Earth has
to pay cannot be measured

00:31:12.950 --> 00:31:17.210 align:middle line:84%
by multiplying the consumption
of a Western man by 6 billion.

00:31:17.210 --> 00:31:18.950 align:middle line:90%
This is not possible.

00:31:18.950 --> 00:31:21.310 align:middle line:90%
Therefore, one has to share.

00:31:21.310 --> 00:31:24.050 align:middle line:84%
And Westerners, who are
costing the Earth the most,

00:31:24.050 --> 00:31:26.270 align:middle line:90%
must change their lifestyle.

00:31:26.270 --> 00:31:30.560 align:middle line:84%
By doing so, they won't even
lose out in terms of happiness.

00:31:30.560 --> 00:31:32.600 align:middle line:84%
The real problem
concerns the issue

00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:34.790 align:middle line:90%
of happiness, not consumerism.

00:31:34.790 --> 00:31:39.660 align:middle line:90%


00:31:39.660 --> 00:31:44.530 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:44.530 --> 00:31:46.000 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:31:46.000 --> 00:32:12.680 align:middle line:90%


00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:14.100 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:32:14.100 --> 00:32:17.220 align:middle line:84%
>> There is no problem
with the cattle.

00:32:17.220 --> 00:32:18.750 align:middle line:84%
However, those who
have bought them

00:32:18.750 --> 00:32:21.150 align:middle line:84%
say they do not eat
the rice they are fed,

00:32:21.150 --> 00:32:23.130 align:middle line:90%
nor do they drink the water.

00:32:23.130 --> 00:32:25.570 align:middle line:84%
They say the cattle
are worthless.

00:32:25.570 --> 00:32:27.210 align:middle line:90%
>> It is not true.

00:32:27.210 --> 00:32:30.360 align:middle line:90%
They eat very well.

00:32:30.360 --> 00:32:31.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Poor things.

00:32:31.530 --> 00:32:35.280 align:middle line:84%
I should have gone on Wednesday
to see how they were doing.

00:32:35.280 --> 00:32:37.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Perhaps they are saying
that because they do not have

00:32:37.830 --> 00:32:41.640 align:middle line:90%
the money to pay for them.

00:32:41.640 --> 00:32:44.616 align:middle line:90%
Look how well they are eating.

00:32:44.616 --> 00:32:45.765 align:middle line:90%
Oh, they are lying.

00:32:45.765 --> 00:33:00.590 align:middle line:90%


00:33:00.590 --> 00:33:04.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Every morning, 5,000 people
from the surrounding villages

00:33:04.820 --> 00:33:08.210 align:middle line:84%
make their way to their
workplaces in Auroville.

00:33:08.210 --> 00:33:10.880 align:middle line:84%
Some Tamils, on the other
hand, have taken the decision

00:33:10.880 --> 00:33:14.810 align:middle line:84%
to take part in this new
project of communal living,

00:33:14.810 --> 00:33:18.800 align:middle line:84%
thus 30% of the population
of Auroville is Indian.

00:33:18.800 --> 00:33:21.755 align:middle line:84%
The other nations represented
are mainly Western ones.

00:33:21.755 --> 00:33:28.520 align:middle line:90%


00:33:28.520 --> 00:33:31.310 align:middle line:84%
>> It's good that I see you,
because I have some clothes

00:33:31.310 --> 00:33:33.500 align:middle line:84%
to be stitched in
the Free Store.

00:33:33.500 --> 00:33:35.258 align:middle line:90%
What time can I come there?

00:33:35.258 --> 00:33:38.126 align:middle line:84%
>> We're open every
morning, 9:00 to 12:00.

00:33:38.126 --> 00:33:40.020 align:middle line:90%
Come Monday morning if you like.

00:33:40.020 --> 00:33:40.820 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:33:40.820 --> 00:33:43.150 align:middle line:84%
So I come on Monday
morning with my things.

00:33:43.150 --> 00:33:44.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Have a nice day.

00:33:44.600 --> 00:33:45.400 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:46.200 align:middle line:90%
You too.

00:33:46.200 --> 00:33:52.590 align:middle line:90%


00:33:52.590 --> 00:33:55.860 align:middle line:84%
>> While still an adolescent,
Raman used to join his father

00:33:55.860 --> 00:33:58.590 align:middle line:84%
working on a number of
different construction sites

00:33:58.590 --> 00:34:00.150 align:middle line:90%
in Auroville.

00:34:00.150 --> 00:34:03.720 align:middle line:84%
Over the years, and following
his decision to join Auroville,

00:34:03.720 --> 00:34:06.210 align:middle line:84%
Raman has gained
professional experience

00:34:06.210 --> 00:34:10.290 align:middle line:84%
in a number of areas, as a
mason, an organic farmer,

00:34:10.290 --> 00:34:12.000 align:middle line:90%
and as an architect.

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:16.080 align:middle line:84%
Today he is becoming experienced
in making documentary videos

00:34:16.080 --> 00:34:18.420 align:middle line:84%
in order to make Tamil
culture, which is

00:34:18.420 --> 00:34:20.889 align:middle line:90%
his own culture, better known.

00:34:20.889 --> 00:34:24.210 align:middle line:84%
However, 30 years ago,
not all the Tamils

00:34:24.210 --> 00:34:27.540 align:middle line:84%
were as enthusiastic as
he was about the arrival

00:34:27.540 --> 00:34:29.880 align:middle line:90%
of Westerners.

00:34:29.880 --> 00:34:31.080 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:34:31.080 --> 00:34:34.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Coming here, we noticed a lot
of what looked like abandoned

00:34:34.170 --> 00:34:36.150 align:middle line:90%
houses.

00:34:36.150 --> 00:34:38.850 align:middle line:84%
>> The villagers have
sold their lands and left.

00:34:38.850 --> 00:34:42.000 align:middle line:84%
See, this street is
now totally empty.

00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:45.210 align:middle line:84%
This village has not developed
with the growth of Auroville.

00:34:45.210 --> 00:34:48.690 align:middle line:84%
Recent arrivals say that
perhaps life has improved,

00:34:48.690 --> 00:34:50.600 align:middle line:84%
but I, who have lived
here for 30 years,

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:53.646 align:middle line:90%
can not say that much.

00:34:53.646 --> 00:35:13.260 align:middle line:10%
[RHYTHMIC MUSIC]

00:35:13.260 --> 00:35:16.350 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:35:16.350 --> 00:35:19.632 align:middle line:84%
>> What was life like here
before the start of Auroville?

00:35:19.632 --> 00:35:21.480 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH].

00:35:21.480 --> 00:35:23.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Now it rains honey.

00:35:23.640 --> 00:35:26.190 align:middle line:90%
Everything has changed a lot.

00:35:26.190 --> 00:35:28.360 align:middle line:84%
Before, people went
around on bicycles.

00:35:28.360 --> 00:35:30.870 align:middle line:90%


00:35:30.870 --> 00:35:35.050 align:middle line:84%
Now you see all sorts
of vehicles on the road.

00:35:35.050 --> 00:35:38.960 align:middle line:84%
Son, you are the only one who
has not profited from all this.

00:35:38.960 --> 00:35:49.580 align:middle line:90%


00:35:49.580 --> 00:35:50.840 align:middle line:90%
>> I was a wanderer.

00:35:50.840 --> 00:35:52.480 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:35:52.480 --> 00:35:55.530 align:middle line:84%
In fact, my dream was
to become a [INAUDIBLE],,

00:35:55.530 --> 00:35:58.630 align:middle line:84%
which, unfortunately, I
could not do [INAUDIBLE]..

00:35:58.630 --> 00:35:59.490 align:middle line:90%
It's different.

00:35:59.490 --> 00:36:00.290 align:middle line:90%
And interesting.

00:36:00.290 --> 00:36:03.960 align:middle line:84%
Auroville is sort of
integrated, you see?

00:36:03.960 --> 00:36:07.980 align:middle line:10%
So you not necessarily need
to express your yoganess

00:36:07.980 --> 00:36:09.600 align:middle line:10%
or yoginess through all this.

00:36:09.600 --> 00:36:10.740 align:middle line:90%
Not traditional.

00:36:10.740 --> 00:36:13.950 align:middle line:84%
Growing beard and not
taking bath and not

00:36:13.950 --> 00:36:15.450 align:middle line:90%
wearing proper clothes.

00:36:15.450 --> 00:36:18.450 align:middle line:84%
The beauty about Auroville is,
you know, you have everything,

00:36:18.450 --> 00:36:22.020 align:middle line:84%
and yet at the same time,
you can be a yogi too.

00:36:22.020 --> 00:36:24.600 align:middle line:84%
I've had a lot of
confidence in me

00:36:24.600 --> 00:36:26.350 align:middle line:84%
that money wouldn't
be a problem.

00:36:26.350 --> 00:36:30.668 align:middle line:84%
And money didn't play the
main role in my life as well.

00:36:30.668 --> 00:36:40.730 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH]

00:36:40.730 --> 00:36:43.040 align:middle line:84%
>> There have been many
changes in our village since

00:36:43.040 --> 00:36:45.350 align:middle line:90%
the inception of Auroville.

00:36:45.350 --> 00:36:47.530 align:middle line:84%
Before people didn't
have any work.

00:36:47.530 --> 00:36:49.910 align:middle line:90%
Now they are all employed.

00:36:49.910 --> 00:36:52.340 align:middle line:84%
Civically, we used
to be very backward,

00:36:52.340 --> 00:36:55.730 align:middle line:84%
but we have progressed
considerably since.

00:36:55.730 --> 00:36:58.280 align:middle line:84%
They started many
handicraft units,

00:36:58.280 --> 00:37:01.610 align:middle line:84%
where we work with leather,
flowers, and candles.

00:37:01.610 --> 00:37:04.270 align:middle line:84%
Things have much improved
because of Auroville.

00:37:04.270 --> 00:37:08.030 align:middle line:90%


00:37:08.030 --> 00:37:10.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Auroville has built the
Mohanam Cultural Center

00:37:10.340 --> 00:37:11.570 align:middle line:90%
in my village.

00:37:11.570 --> 00:37:14.370 align:middle line:84%
It is a good example of
what Auroville can do.

00:37:14.370 --> 00:37:16.430 align:middle line:84%
Through Mohanam, they've
established a model

00:37:16.430 --> 00:37:18.770 align:middle line:84%
to infuse new life into
an ancient culture.

00:37:18.770 --> 00:37:22.350 align:middle line:90%


